<sect1 id="IsLeapYear">
  <title><emphasis role="bold">IsLeapYear</emphasis></title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Date.IsLeapYear<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Date.IsLeapYear</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>Date.IsLeapYear</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>year</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="0" frame="none" rowsep="0">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>year</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>A year value in the INTEGER2 format.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Return:</entry>

          <entry>IsLeapYear returns a BOOLEAN value.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">IsLeapYear</emphasis> function returns TRUE if the <emphasis>year</emphasis> is 
  a leap year in the Gregorian (or proleptic Gregorian) calendar.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
INTEGER2 MyYear := 2012;   //2012
  
D := STD.Date.IsLeapYear(MyYear);
    //D contains TRUE, 2012 is a leap year
  </programlisting>

  <para></para>
</sect1>
